{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/vop/DASH--look_at-1.0/DASH-look_at-icon.svg", "type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "look_at", "version": "1.0", "namespace": "DASH"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Look At Rotation Matrix (aim+pole)"], "extent": [38, 75]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Define a orthonormal 3\u00d73 matrix based on two directions, matching one of them."], "extent": [75, 162]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [162, 177], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This is a repackaging of ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/lookat", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "lookat()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/lookat.html"}, "(), addressing minor inconviniences with either function or VOP:"], "extent": [177, 280]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["No need to negate the forward direction, unlike the native method: ", {"type": "code", "text": ["lookat(0, -fwd, up)"]}, ", since the operation was built for cameras, which point at things with -Z."], "extent": [280, 446]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "ui", "text": ["From"]}, " removed since it has a non-zero defult in VOP. Positions can be contextualized into proper directions with Subtract beforehand."], "extent": [446, 586]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["At the core, the ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/lookat", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "lookat()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/lookat.html"}, "() is a double cross product, that conveniently takes care of the special cases where that would naturally fail. The ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["case"]}]}, " output reports those. This operation can quickly provide perpendicular vector directions, through the axes outputs."], "extent": [586, 860]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For further conceptual understanding of the operation itself, check ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/DASH--lookat_didactic-1.0", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/DASH--lookat_didactic-1.0.html"}, " SOP and this ", {"scheme": null, "value": "https://youtu.be/EASQphcIn38?t=1820", "type": "link", "text": ["video"], "exists": true}, "."], "extent": [860, 1024]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1024, 1036], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Forward Direction"], "extent": [1036, 1056], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Direction of Z axis or Forward direction of the output 3\u00d73 matrix."], "extent": [1093, 1165]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "forward_u1"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Direction"], "extent": [1165, 1179], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This direction will be projected to a plane defined by ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Forward Direction"]}, ", normalized and become the output matrix\u2019s Y axis or second row."], "extent": [1206, 1353]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up_u2"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Main Direction"], "extent": [1353, 1369], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["By default the output matrix Z axis will match the input Forward\u2019s direction. By changing this to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Up"]}, ", it will be the output matrix Y axis that will be matching the input Up instead."], "extent": [1408, 1596]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 4, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--look_at-1.0/DASH-look_at-help_main_direction.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [1596, 1659], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "wide left"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "main_dir_v4"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Array Auto Resize"], "extent": [1688, 1714], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Common Size"], "extent": [1714, 1727], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["Determines the size that all input arrays will have. ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Min"]}, " will use the smallest array\u2019s size, while ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Max"]}, " will use the greatest array\u2019s size."], "extent": [1756, 1906]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_size"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fill"], "extent": [1906, 1912], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["Sized up arrays need a fill value. This determines whether the fill is the parameter\u2019s ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Default"]}, " or, if the array is not empty, its ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Last"]}, " or ", {"type": "em", "text": ["First"]}, " value."], "extent": [1941, 2101]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_fill"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [2101, 2111], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Description"], "extent": [2111, 2124], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["String to display info on top of the node in the network view. The pilcrow \u00b6 button enables multi-line text."], "extent": [2143, 2255]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "description"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", 